# HeapVortex - Main Application Component

## Overview

This file serves as the main entry point of the **HeapVortex** application. It combines a real-time 3D heap visualization with an interactive telemetry dashboard, providing users with an immersive JVM memory profiling experience.

The application is built using **React**, **TypeScript**, **React Three Fiber**, **Three.js**, and **Tailwind CSS** to create a modern and responsive interface.

---

## Features

- Full-screen interactive 3D visualization
- Real-time heap object rendering
- Orbit camera controls for navigation
- Dynamic star-field background
- Realistic lighting effects
- Live telemetry sidebar
- JVM connection status indicator
- Bottom HUD displaying heap statistics
- Loading indicator while 3D assets initialize
- Responsive overlay UI using Tailwind CSS

---

## Project Structure

```
src/
│
├── App.tsx
├── features/
│   ├── 3d-view/
│   │   └── components/
│   │       └── HeapScene.tsx
│   │
│   └── telemetry/
│       └── components/
│           └── TelemetrySidebar.tsx
```

---

## Technologies Used

- React
- TypeScript
- Three.js
- React Three Fiber
- React Drei
- Tailwind CSS

---

## Component Architecture

### App Component

The `App` component acts as the root container of the application and manages the overall layout.

It consists of three major sections:

### 1. 3D Visualization Layer

Responsible for rendering the interactive JVM heap scene.

Includes:

- Canvas
- Perspective Camera
- Orbit Controls
- Stars Environment
- Ambient Light
- Point Light
- Spot Light
- HeapScene Component

---

### 2. UI Overlay Layer

Displays interactive dashboard components above the 3D canvas.

Contains:

- Application Header
- Telemetry Sidebar
- JVM Agent Status
- Heap Statistics HUD

---

### 3. Loader

Displays loading progress while the 3D scene initializes.

---

## Layout Strategy

The application uses layered positioning for a clean visualization experience.

```
+-----------------------------------------------------+
|                  UI Overlay Layer                   |
|                                                     |
|  Sidebar      Status Panel        Bottom HUD        |
|                                                     |
+-----------------------------------------------------+

                ▲

+-----------------------------------------------------+
|                3D Canvas Layer                      |
|                                                     |
|        Heap Objects + Camera + Lighting             |
|                                                     |
+-----------------------------------------------------+
```

---

## Camera Configuration

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Type | Perspective Camera |
| Position | (0, 5, 15) |
| Field of View | 75° |

Users can freely rotate, zoom, and inspect the heap visualization using OrbitControls.

---

## Lighting Setup

The application uses multiple light sources to enhance scene realism.

### Ambient Light

Provides soft illumination across the entire scene.

### Point Light

Simulates a directional light source with shadow support.

### Spot Light

Adds focused illumination to emphasize heap structures.

---

## UI Components

### Telemetry Sidebar

Displays live JVM telemetry information, including:

- Heap usage
- Memory allocation
- JVM metrics
- Performance statistics

---

### Connection Status

Shows the runtime connection state of the JVM Agent.

Example:

```
Agent Connected: PID 12408
```

---

### Bottom HUD

Displays quick heap statistics.

Example metrics:

- Total Objects
- Heap Used
- GC Pause Time

---

## Reusable Components

### StatItem

A reusable component used for displaying statistics consistently throughout the application.

Properties:

| Prop | Description |
|------|-------------|
| label | Metric name |
| value | Metric value |

Example:

```
Objects
12,402
```

---

